# L10N.md Standard

> {{ site.description }} L10N.md keeps a small machine-readable surface in YAML frontmatter and pushes nuance into Markdown prose so AI translation systems can read the context that translators provide.

This site publishes the L10N.md specification (currently version {{ site.spec.version }}, status {{ site.spec.status | lower }}) and the canonical JSON Schema files that define a conforming document. The same content is available as rendered HTML and as the source Markdown.

## Specification

{% for l in spec.locales %}- [Specification v{{ spec.version }} ({{ l.label }})]({{ site.url }}/v{{ spec.version }}/{% if l.code != 'en' %}{{ l.code }}/{% endif %}): full rendered specification.
- [Specification v{{ spec.version }} ({{ l.label }}, Markdown)]({{ site.url }}/v{{ spec.version }}/{% if l.code != 'en' %}{{ l.code }}/{% endif %}spec.md): single concatenated Markdown bundle of every section, suitable for ingestion by AI agents.
{% endfor %}

## JSON Schemas (version {{ spec.version }})

- [Entry schema]({{ site.url }}/schemas/v{{ spec.version }}/l10n-document.schema.json): `oneOf` over the three document shapes.
- [Global document schema]({{ site.url }}/schemas/v{{ spec.version }}/global-document.schema.json): the repository root `L10N.md`.
- [Scoped document schema]({{ site.url }}/schemas/v{{ spec.version }}/scoped-document.schema.json): a nested `L10N.md`.
- [Locale overlay schema]({{ site.url }}/schemas/v{{ spec.version }}/locale-overlay.schema.json): a per-language file under `L10N/`.
- [Shared definitions]({{ site.url }}/schemas/v{{ spec.version }}/shared.schema.json): reusable types, including the BCP 47 locale identifier.

